soln_description:
This is a classic induction exercise:

- Initialization The property is true for $n=1$, since $1 \leq 2-\frac{1}{1}$. Note that the number 2 only appears in this initialization phase; however, it plays a fundamental role in the result.
- Heredity If the property is true for $n$, then it is true for $n+1$ because:

$$
\begin{gathered}
\left(1+\cdots+\frac{1}{n^{2}}\right)+\frac{1}{(n+1)^{2}} \leq\left(2-\frac{1}{n}\right)+\frac{1}{(n+1)^{2}} \\
\leq\left(2-\frac{1}{n}\right)+\frac{1}{n(n+1)}=2-\frac{1}{n+1}
\end{gathered}
$$

